  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_a3eef3e670e30eb955ec8c646fe4c89e">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Records of the Acquisitions Dept. include correspondence of Felix Reichmann and Arthur Sweet; miscellaneous correspondence; general correspondence and fund books (1898-1948); and correspondence with vendors, 1985-1986.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_075059ee1353df383caddf0513325fb7">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Accessions volumes (1874-1948), including Andrew Dickson White's personal library, 1881-1891 (vol. 3), Zarncke Library, 1893-1899 (vol. 11), Thurston Collection, 1905 (vol. 24), Barnes Collection, 1913-1947 (vols. 49-50),  Comstock Library, 1914-1947 (vols. 52-53), Goldwin Smith Library, 1907-1947 (vols. 54-56); Wason Collection, 1918-1947 (vols. 63-64); Dante Collection, 1907-1947 (vols. 66-67); Petrarch Collection, 1907-1943 (vol. 65); and Maps, 1898-1946 (vols. 87-88) Also, Chemistry Library accession books (7 vols., 1927-1962); Latin Seminary accession book, (1892-1914); and catalog of the Franz Bopp collection.</p>  </scopecontent>
